column9:
The current implementation performs an O(n²) operation by using `some()` inside `filter()`. Consider using a `Set` for better performance:
```typescript
const modifiedFiles = new Set(incrementalDiff.data.files.map(f => f.filename));
filesToReview = filesToReview.filter(file => modifiedFiles.has(file.filename));
```
This approach reduces the time complexity to O(n) and makes the code more readable.

